    <div class="section">
      <h2>What is Black Obsidian?</h2>
      <p>Black Obsidian is a powerful, volcanic glass formed through the rapid cooling of lava. Its rich black color and mirror-like surface have made it a favorite in spiritual and healing practices. Often considered a grounding stone, Black Obsidian is used to uncover hidden truths and release negative energy.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Properties & Benefits</h2>
      <p>Known for its intense protective qualities, Black Obsidian helps to shield against negativity and emotional trauma. It encourages self-reflection, clears away confusion, and aids in the release of deeply held emotions. As a grounding stone, it helps in establishing a strong connection with the Earth and supports resilience in times of adversity.</p>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Uses of Black Obsidian</h2>
      <ul>
        <li><strong>Meditation:</strong> Black Obsidian is often used to deepen meditation practices by focusing on self-awareness and healing.</li>
        <li><strong>Jewelry:</strong> Worn as a protective amulet or in rings, bracelets, and necklaces.</li>
        <li><strong>Home Decor:</strong> Placed in spaces to create a protective aura, dispelling negativity.</li>
        <li><strong>Scrying:</strong> Due to its reflective surface, Black Obsidian is popular in divination and scrying practices.</li>
      </ul>
    </div>

    <div class="section">
      <h2>Meaning of Black Obsidian</h2>
      <p>Black Obsidian is considered the "Stone of Truth." It brings to light aspects of oneself that may be hidden, promoting clarity, strength, and courage to confront them. A powerful tool for spiritual cleansing, it allows one to move forward with a greater understanding of their personal journey and sense of purpose.</p>
    </div>

